This paper is about face de-identification, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and privacy (cs.CR). The proposed approach uses GAN, which is a popular machine learning technique for image generation and manipulation, and involves designing novel verificator and regulator modules, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions adapting GAN with priors of domain knowledge, which could also relate to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
